cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.HC

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with video recognition and data augmentation using video transforms. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a general approach to discover invariant classes and novel-generating classes, which involves learning from transformed videos. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category as the paper deals with video transforms and their impact on video recognition. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper proposes a new approach to data augmentation and zero-shot learning using label-transforms. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also a possible category as the paper includes a human perception study to validate the realism of time-reversed videos.
